      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2021 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented QA procedures, regression test suites, and ISO 9001 certification. FDA in-house solver version control and verification logs were reviewed and confirmed compliant with required gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems including cantilever beam bending and contact patch tests were executed against analytical solutions. Residual norms converged to machine precision. All three ensemble solvers passed numerical code verification benchmarks at gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed on the pedicle screw and rod assembly. Three mesh densities evaluated; Richardson extrapolation applied to peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod interface. Grid convergence index below 2% for the finest mesh, satisfying gradation 3 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence monitored via force and displacement residuals. Tight convergence tolerances (1e-6 relative) applied. Iterative solver settings verified against direct solver reference solutions for representative load steps. No solver divergence events observed across the ensemble."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Independent model review conducted by a second analyst at each participating organisation. Boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application were cross-checked against the simulation protocol document. No use errors identified following review."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic isotropic material models used for titanium alloy components; validated against published coupon data. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod interface supported by tribological literature. Model form assumptions documented and justified relative to the quasi-static compression-bending regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34 for Ti-6Al-4V) sourced from ASTM B265 certified mill certificates for the test lot. Geometry extracted from calibrated CMM measurements of the actual test specimens. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo sampling; coefficient of variation below 3% for all critical inputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Samples drawn from the same production lot; dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to design drawings. Sample size sufficient for gradation 3 per ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 guidance for medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single loading configuration (compression-bending at 5 degrees per ASTM F1717). Only one test condition was evaluated; multi-angle or multi-rate conditions were not included in this validation activity. Achieved gradation 2 is below the required gradation 3, representing the one identified gap in this credibility assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
