      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters mapped one-to-one to measured experimental conditions. Loading fixture geometry, crosshead displacement rate, and specimen mounting replicated in the FEA boundary conditions. Equivalency confirmed through a formal parameter mapping table reviewed by all three ensemble teams."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted construct stiffness and yield load compared against experimental means using normalised error metrics. All three ensemble predictions fell within 10% of experimental mean; 95% prediction intervals overlapped experimental distributions. Graphical and statistical comparisons documented in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Quantities of interest (construct stiffness, yield load, peak screw-rod interface stress) directly correspond to the mechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and are clinically relevant indicators of spinal fixation construct integrity. Relevance to the decision context confirmed by the clinical and regulatory team."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the physical test protocol (ASTM F1717) that defines the regulatory submission test for posterior spinal fixation devices. The validation scenario is therefore directly relevant to the intended regulatory and clinical research application of the model, supporting the overall credibility argument despite the single-condition limitation in Test conditions."
    }
